Warm oil in a large nonstick saucepan over medium heat. Add pork and cook until no longer pink. Stir in bell pepper, onion, garlic, chile peppers, chili powder, cumin, black pepper, and red pepper. Cook 8 minutes, or until vegetables are tender. Stir in diced tomatoes (with juice), diced tomatoes with chiles (with juice), kidney beans, and black beans. Cook 10 to 15 minutes, or until flavors are blended.